aring For June 14, 2022. FIRST OF THREE READINGS Finance 5/12/22, 4-0 Sponsors: Eric Stuckey, Kristine Brock, Michael Walters Young<br /><br />16. Consideration Of Ordinance 2022-14, An Ordinance Of The City Of Franklin, Tennessee To Amend Appendix A - Comprehensive Fees And Penalties, Chapter 17 Refuse And Trash Disposal, Of The Franklin Municipal Code To Increase The Fees For Collection Of Garbage And Refuse. Establishing A Public Hearing For June 14, 2022. FIRST OF THREE READINGS<br />Finance 5/12/22, 4-0 Sponsors: Eric Stuckey, Mark Hilty, Kristine Brock, Michael Walters Young<br /><br />17. *Consideration Of Resolution 2022-35, A Resolution To Amend The Franklin Police Department<br />Wrecker Service Policy And Agreement.<br />Sponsors: Deb Faulkner<br />ALL OTHER CONSENT ITEMS<br /><br />CITY OFFICES CLOSED \u2013 Memorial Day<br />Capital Investment Committee FMPC & BOMA Joint Workshop Franklin Planning Commission<br /><br />OTHER BUSINESS ADJOURN<br />Anyone needing accommodations due to disabilities please contact the Risk Manager at 615-791-3277 24-hours prior to the meeting.<br /><br />#CityofFranklin #FranklinTN #BoardMeeting",
